THE MEMORIAL TOURNAMENT PRESENTED BY NATIONWIDE INSURANCE
June 5, 2011
Steve Stricker
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT









   STEVE STRICKER: It was a little bit of a struggle since we came out after the rain delay. You know, at that point I'm just trying not to make a mistake. I had a couple opportunities early on, and I wish those putts would have gone in, would have freed me up a little bit. But I hung tough and hit a couple crucial putts when I had to.

 Q. Is this the greatest win of your career?
 STEVE STRICKER: Yeah, it's pretty special walking off and --

 Q. That man over there?
 STEVE STRICKER: No doubt about it. He's a friend, and it's truly an honor. 







